.-Benett_Dave-Benett_Getty-Images-for-Hartmann-House-Ltd.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Conor-Maynard.-CREDIT_-David-M.-Benett_Dave-Benett_Getty-Images-for-Hartmann-House-Ltd.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Conor-Maynard.-CREDIT_-David-M.-Benett_Dave-Benett_Getty-Images-for-Hartmann-House-Ltd-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Conor-Maynard.-CREDIT_-David-M.-Benett_Dave-Benett_Getty-Images-for-Hartmann-House-Ltd-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Conor-Maynard.-CREDIT_-David-M.-Benett_Dave-Benett_Getty-Images-for-Hartmann-House-Ltd-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Conor-Maynard.-CREDIT_-David-M.-Benett_Dave-Benett_Getty-Images-for-Hartmann-House-Ltd-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Conor-Maynard.-CREDIT_-David-M.-Benett_Dave-Benett_Getty-Images-for-Hartmann-House-Ltd-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> Conor Maynard has issued a health update after he was rushed to hospital over the weekend.</p><p> Taking to Instagram yesterday evening (February 16), Maynard explained that he had fallen down a flight of stairs during the day and ended up having to take a trip to the hospital via an ambulance.</p><p> The first image in a series of photos posted to his story sees him lying on a stretcher, with straps around his face and arms and his neck in a brace, alongside the caption “Sunday funday”.</p><p> Another video, also taken on Sunday evening, shows him being wheeled outside his home on a stretcher by two paramedics. The singer gave no details, aside from the caption, “FML” and a laughing emoji.</p><p> Finally, he posted an image of him back at home with his thumb up, writing: “I&#39;m doing ok guys. You&#39;re not allowed to laugh … but I fell down some stairs.</p><p> “But nothing too serious, you can breathe now.” </p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr"><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f6a8.png" alt="🚨" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/15.0.3/72x72/1f1ec-1f1e7.png" alt="🇬🇧" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> | CONOR MAYNARD RUSHED TO HOSPITAL</p><p> Conor Maynard shares a picture from the hospital after a serious accident, leaving fans concerned for his health.</p><p> • The Sun <a href="https://t.co/sgbjOuLflI">pic.twitter.com/sgbjOuLflI</a></p><p> — Leil (@LeilIdeas) <a href="https://twitter.com/LeilIdeas/status/1891482983388876945?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">February 17, 2025</a> </p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p> Conor Maynard first found fame in 2008 when he began posting covers of popular tracks on YouTube, with his take on Ne-Yo&#39;s &#39;Beautiful Monster&#39; gaining the attention of the singer. Ne-Yo would later mentor Maynard, and led Maynard to signing with EMI/Parlophone and management company Turn First.</p><p> His debut single &#39;Can&#39;t Say No&#39; shot to Number 2 in the UK charts, shortly after being followed up by &#39;Vegas Girl&#39;, which reached Number 4.</p><p> <em>NME</em> <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/reviews-various-artists-13501-305345">reviewed his debut album &#39;Contrast&#39; in 2012</a> , and reflected on his reputation at the time as the “British [Justin] Bieber”, writing: “The tag does the Brighton native a disservice, as it&#39;s another Justin that the choicer moments of &#39;Contrasts&#39; call to mind – Timberlake, at his thrusting, braggadocio-laden best.”</p><p> He&#39;s released two further albums since then, the latest being his 2023 record &#39;+11 Hours&#39;.</p><p> Maynard&#39;s most recent single &#39;She&#39;s So High&#39; – a collaboration with German D Jaxamony – came out earlier this year.</p><p></p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/conor-maynard-issues-health-update-after-being-rushed-to-hospital-3838665">Conor Maynard issues health update after being rushed to hospital</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
